WEBVTT

00:07.137 --> 00:10.749
[dramatic, menacing music]

00:13.883 --> 00:16.233
[no audio]

00:18.757 --> 00:23.632
[people chattering]
[laughing]

00:44.696 --> 00:48.787
-When Abaddon the angel fell,

00:48.918 --> 00:52.226
he made his home in
the depths of Hell,

00:53.488 --> 00:56.926
alone and full of dark despair.

00:57.057 --> 01:01.278
He defied the god
who'd sent him there.

01:01.409 --> 01:04.325
Escaping from his fiery den,

01:04.455 --> 01:08.894
he clawed his way
to the land of men.

01:09.025 --> 01:13.073
In the guise of a pauper,
he lived his days,

01:13.203 --> 01:16.989
unseen by God's selective gaze.

01:18.208 --> 01:21.690
Lost and alone, a
one-winged dove,

01:22.995 --> 01:26.260
he met a woman and
found true love.

01:27.391 --> 01:30.177
Playing tricks for
her, the Devil's art,

01:30.307 --> 01:33.615
and soon enough,
he'd won her heart.

01:35.095 --> 01:39.708
But bodies fade and rot inside

01:39.838 --> 01:43.277
and by and by, his lover died.

01:44.365 --> 01:47.803
Enraged, the Devil
ripped his guise

01:47.933 --> 01:51.241
and yelled up to the holy skies.

01:52.416 --> 01:56.116
God awoke in a perilous fit

01:56.246 --> 02:00.729
and dragged the Devil
back to his pit.

02:02.339 --> 02:06.169
But he clung to his love,
his claws pulled her asunder

02:06.300 --> 02:11.131
'til God pushed him down and
the dark sucked him under.

02:13.045 --> 02:16.005
Vultures picked at the body.

02:17.049 --> 02:18.616
God watched the theft

02:19.704 --> 02:24.535
'til only the bones and
her heart were left.

02:26.233 --> 02:30.062
And while God slept,
the heart revived

02:31.107 --> 02:36.025
with the Devil's
needle lodged inside.

02:36.156 --> 02:39.463
Know this, the Devil
has his friends,

02:39.594 --> 02:43.859
the murderers, thieves,
the odds and ends,

02:43.989 --> 02:47.950
the quiet and broken,
the brutally flawed

02:48.080 --> 02:52.172
who slip beneath
the eyes of God.

02:53.260 --> 02:57.046
And so the heart
was lost 'til found

02:57.177 --> 02:59.918
and through the
ages passed around

03:00.049 --> 03:03.966
by those who like to cut and sew

03:04.096 --> 03:07.622
while the Devil guides
them from below,

03:07.752 --> 03:11.103
to hide the heart
in flesh and bone

03:11.234 --> 03:14.498
so the Devil will
no more be alone.

03:15.847 --> 03:19.938
And they sing this
song soft and sweet

03:20.069 --> 03:24.204
to keep the heavens
sound asleep.

03:26.510 --> 03:30.688
When the road is mean,
blood will thicken.

03:32.124 --> 03:36.216
The Devil's pulse
begins to quicken.

03:37.521 --> 03:42.134
While the body rots
to dust and bones,

03:43.440 --> 03:47.183
there's a tear in the heart
where the Devil roams.

03:48.880 --> 03:52.144
[audience applauding]

