three throws for a nickel.

13:09.005 --> 13:10.354
Three throws for
a nickel, folks,

13:10.485 --> 13:13.749
three throws for a nickel,
hit them cats down.

13:13.880 --> 13:15.795
-So what's the
scam with this one?

13:15.925 --> 13:16.839
-No scam.

13:16.970 --> 13:18.362
-Cat heavy or the ball light?

13:18.493 --> 13:20.408
-Why don't you slap down
a nickel and find out.

13:20.538 --> 13:23.977
-[laughs] Lady, I didn't get
this farm playing the fool.

13:25.848 --> 13:26.980
You have a good night.

13:28.503 --> 13:30.810
-Three throws for
a nickel, folks,

13:30.940 --> 13:33.029
three throws for a nickel.

13:36.293 --> 13:40.645
-Oh Lord, what time I cry
in the night before thee?

13:42.256 --> 13:45.259
For my soul is
sated with troubles

13:46.434 --> 13:49.132
and my life draweth
nigh until the grave.

13:50.264 --> 13:54.224
I've called upon thee,
oh Lord, every day!

13:54.355 --> 13:57.358
I have spread forth
my hands unto thee.

13:57.488 --> 14:02.450
Thou hast laid me in the
nether-most pit, in dark places,

14:03.886 --> 14:05.018
in the deeps.

14:06.019 --> 14:07.934
Set apart among the dead!

14:09.152 --> 14:12.068
Like the slain that
lie in the grave

14:12.199 --> 14:15.202
whom now remembers no more!

14:15.332 --> 14:17.726
-Everyone's here
for Mister Tipps.

14:17.857 --> 14:21.208
-They're cut off from my hand.

14:22.644 --> 14:27.649
[distant people chattering]
[children playing]

14:32.001 --> 14:33.873
[scissors snip]
[audience gasps]

14:34.003 --> 14:37.093
I have born thy terrors.
[finger clatter]

14:37.224 --> 14:41.706
Thy terrors have cut me off.
[finger clatters]

14:41.837 --> 14:43.491
[scissors snip]
[finger clatters]

14:43.621 --> 14:45.536
Lord, why casteth off my soul?

14:46.842 --> 14:49.236
Why hidest thou
thy face from me?

14:51.064 --> 14:53.414
Shall thy mercy be
declared in the grave?

14:53.544 --> 14:55.677
[child screams]

14:55.807 --> 14:58.636
Or thy faithfulness
in destruction?

14:58.767 --> 15:03.641
[audience applauds]
[cheers]

15:05.382 --> 15:10.213
[carefree, strumming music]
[fire crackling]

15:15.001 --> 15:20.006
[carefree strumming continues]
[fire crackling]

15:22.399 --> 15:25.446
-Miss Rocky, you sure can
make that little guitar sing.

15:25.576 --> 15:26.795
-Nah.
-It's true.

15:26.926 --> 15:28.492
I'd kill for that
kind of talent.

15:28.623 --> 15:31.365
-Well, you're a better
crowd than tonight's.

15:31.495 --> 15:32.496
It was a hard one.

15:32.627 --> 15:34.194
-Well they sure like Mr. Tipps.

15:34.324 --> 15:37.327
[speaking foreign language]

15:37.458 --> 15:38.633
-How's he do that?

15:38.763 --> 15:40.200
-He's a magician,
that's what they do.

15:40.330 --> 15:42.680
-That ain't magic,
he's kissing the Devil.

15:44.900 --> 15:49.731
[gentle, strumming music]
[fire crackling]

15:55.519 --> 15:56.999
-Mm, that sound is
better than ice cream

15:57.130 --> 15:58.609
on a hot summer day.

15:58.740 --> 16:01.873
[speaking foreign language]

16:02.004 --> 16:03.005
-Why don't you take it, Maggie?

16:03.136 --> 16:04.224
Have some fun with it.

16:04.354 --> 16:05.834
-I can't take
your little guitar.

16:05.965 --> 16:07.183
-Sure you can.

16:07.314 --> 16:08.968
You know, if you learn
how to play good,

16:09.098 --> 16:11.013
you might get invited to
the Buffalo Horror Show.

16:11.144 --> 16:14.495
-[chuckles] Nah, we're
just a little side act.

16:14.625 --> 16:18.064
-Ah, [speaks foreign language]

16:18.194 --> 16:20.283
-Take it, I got three others.

16:21.937 --> 16:24.679
[fire crackling]

16:31.599 --> 16:34.950
[out of tune strumming]

16:37.997 --> 16:43.002
[distant dog barking]
[out of tune strumming]

16:44.960 --> 16:48.311
[quiet, menacing music]

16:53.751 --> 16:57.712
[quiet menacing music continues]

17:03.718 --> 17:06.721
[quiet, menacing
music continues]

17:06.851 --> 17:08.288
-You're letting in the cold.

17:10.899 --> 17:11.987
Come in.

17:12.118 --> 17:15.773
[quiet, menacing music]

17:15.904 --> 17:18.559
Time to fix the tips.

17:19.951 --> 17:20.996
Wanna watch?

17:23.085 --> 17:25.000
Devil knows you
can keep a secret.

17:26.045 --> 17:29.396
[quiet, menacing music]

17:37.056 --> 17:40.537
When I was a boy,
I loved the circus.

17:42.887 --> 17:44.063
Every summer, when
it came to town,

17:44.193 --> 17:46.152
my mother would
give me five pennies

17:47.283 --> 17:49.155
to see the show
under the big top.

17:50.939 --> 17:54.334
The Strong Man, ladies
riding the elephants,

17:56.162 --> 17:59.600
and the acrobats,
flying through the air.

18:03.343 --> 18:05.519
I saw a man drop to his death.

18:07.912 --> 18:12.221
His brains flew out
of his head like

18:12.352 --> 18:15.268
cotton candy, all pink and
soft, all over the crowd.

18:16.443 --> 18:19.098
And a lion eat the
arm off a little girl.

18:20.490 --> 18:22.666
[chuckles] I saw Rizzo the
Wizzo take her final ride

18:22.797 --> 18:28.019
through her meat cannon, her
insides now on the outside.

18:29.195 --> 18:32.111
[chuckles] But I longed
for something different,

18:33.286 --> 18:35.505
a ticket away from
my mother's tears,

18:37.159 --> 18:38.682
my father's fists.

18:41.598 --> 18:42.425
Magic.

18:47.561 --> 18:50.781
And I found it
[quiet, menacing music]

18:50.912 --> 18:52.305
in this small tent,

18:53.958 --> 18:55.612
on a battered little stage,

18:58.659 --> 18:59.921
not unlike yours.

19:01.749 --> 19:04.447
A man by the name of Broken Cane

19:07.015 --> 19:11.193
who performed acts,
small and sickening,

19:12.586 --> 19:16.024
a pinky, a big toe, snip, snip,

19:16.155 --> 19:19.549
and the very next
show, they'd be back.

19:19.680 --> 19:20.985
He's no rabbit puller,

19:22.378 --> 19:23.597
no card counter.

19:28.210 --> 19:31.648
How'd he do that?
[distant dog barks]

19:31.779 --> 19:33.563
I just had to know.

19:35.043 --> 19:40.048
So I watched and I
listened, and one night,

19:41.136 --> 19:43.007
he told me the
story of Abaddon--

19:44.574 --> 19:46.620
[distant dog barking]

19:46.750 --> 19:48.012
And the magic heart.

19:49.100 --> 19:52.582
It was a burden he
was happy to unload.

19:54.193 --> 19:57.979
And when he stank
of wine and piss,

20:00.460 --> 20:05.160
I took his magic
and made my own pact

20:07.336 --> 20:09.991
with the darkness.
[quiet, menacing music]

20:10.121 --> 20:13.255
But I'm not greedy,
I stick to the tips.

20:14.343 --> 20:17.607
Only the tips.
[flesh squelches]

20:17.738 --> 20:20.523
When you dance with the Devil,
you gotta make it quick.

20:22.221 --> 20:25.920
So I sing a lullaby,
soft and sweet,

20:27.008 --> 20:30.490
to keep the heavens
sound asleep.

20:35.495 --> 20:37.410
[distant dog barking]

20:37.540 --> 20:41.240
When the road is mean,
blood will thicken.

20:42.371 --> 20:45.461
The Devil's pulse
begins to quicken

20:46.941 --> 20:50.510
while the body rots
to dust and bones.

20:52.033 --> 20:57.081
There's a tear in the heart
where the Devil roams.

20:57.734 --> 21:00.215
[quiet, dark music]

21:03.087 --> 21:05.002
That's a powerful psalm, honey.

21:06.439 --> 21:10.312
[distant dog barking]
[quiet, dark music]

21:10.443 --> 21:14.011
Don't get any ideas, missy,
Devil and me got a deal.

21:15.665 --> 21:17.276
Needs to be heard anyway,

21:18.364 --> 21:21.497
sweet as the breeze
in Abaddon's ear.

21:21.628 --> 21:24.587
[quiet, dark music]

21:24.718 --> 21:25.545
Get out.

21:27.416 --> 21:30.463
