will you shut it?

22:03.409 --> 22:04.453
-Seven, you in?

22:04.584 --> 22:05.541
I'm making you pay
a buck to play.

22:05.672 --> 22:06.890
-Eh, ain't your bet to make.

22:07.021 --> 22:08.370
It's your bet, Ned.

22:08.501 --> 22:09.763
-I'm out.

22:09.893 --> 22:11.199
-It's my bet now.

22:13.244 --> 22:16.639
Two doll hairs.
[dog barking]

22:19.555 --> 22:20.687
-I'm in.

22:20.817 --> 22:23.037
-All right, let's see 'em.

22:23.167 --> 22:28.303
[dog barking]
[wind hissing]

22:30.044 --> 22:32.394
[laughs] Oh, that's
hard to beat.

22:34.744 --> 22:35.615
-That's a good hand.

22:38.661 --> 22:40.141
-Lay 'em on the table, Seven.

22:42.099 --> 22:44.667
-[laughs] Oh,
that's gotta hurt.

22:44.798 --> 22:46.800
Best hand you've had all night
and it ain't good enough.

22:46.930 --> 22:48.497
-Hold on, hold on, hold on.

22:49.759 --> 22:51.239
You know what, he's cheating.

22:51.370 --> 22:53.197
-Bull shit.
-He's fucking cheating.

22:53.328 --> 22:55.591
-[chuckles] Don't let
Maggie catch you saying that.

22:55.722 --> 22:57.114
-He didn't cheat.

22:57.245 --> 22:59.552
-I ain't won a hand
this whole circuit,

22:59.682 --> 23:01.858
and every night you go
home with my earnings?

23:01.989 --> 23:03.512
No, fuck that.

23:03.643 --> 23:04.339
You're a cheat.

23:04.470 --> 23:05.122
-Mm.

23:05.296 --> 23:06.646
-He ain't cheating.

23:07.864 --> 23:12.913
Seven's just not a [smacks
lips] lobotomy prodigy. [laughs]

23:13.609 --> 23:14.567
-You saying I'm stupid?

23:14.697 --> 23:16.612
-No, but you are a clown.

23:16.743 --> 23:20.224
[jarring, dramatic music]

23:24.533 --> 23:25.752
-Holy shit.

23:25.882 --> 23:27.188
[jarring, dramatic music]

23:27.318 --> 23:28.711
Maggie!

23:28.842 --> 23:29.930
[bodies clattering]
[dramatic, distorted music]

23:30.060 --> 23:33.150
Maggie.
[dramatic, distorted music]

23:33.281 --> 23:34.804
[fist smacks]
[body clatters]

23:34.935 --> 23:35.979
Maggie.

23:39.679 --> 23:40.506
-Don't!

23:41.985 --> 23:43.204
S'cuse us, Ned.

23:43.334 --> 23:45.685
[dog barking]

23:47.034 --> 23:49.210
Shh, you okay now, lover.

23:50.254 --> 23:54.650
You're okay.
[dog barking]

23:54.781 --> 23:58.437
[shuffling, fast footsteps]

24:01.135 --> 24:04.443
[distant guns blasting]

24:08.185 --> 24:09.535
-Get rid of it, cut it off.

24:10.753 --> 24:12.276
-Kid, I don't have a full kit.

24:13.408 --> 24:15.976
This is not the place,
I don't have Morphine.

24:16.106 --> 24:17.543
-Cut it off or I'm dead.

24:17.673 --> 24:20.241
[distant guns blasting]

24:20.371 --> 24:22.025
-Stretchers are gonna be here.

24:22.156 --> 24:24.071
[gun blasts]
-I'll be dead by then.

24:24.854 --> 24:25.638
Cut it off.

24:26.943 --> 24:27.770
-What's your name?

24:27.901 --> 24:28.945
-Sully.

24:30.033 --> 24:31.905
-Sully, can you feel this?

24:33.254 --> 24:34.864
-I don't know.
[distant guns blasting]

24:34.995 --> 24:36.387
-Where are you from, Sully?

24:37.301 --> 24:38.302
-Wisconsin.

24:41.044 --> 24:42.219
-Can you do this?

24:42.350 --> 24:43.394
-Do it.

24:43.525 --> 24:46.659
[distant guns blasting]

24:48.008 --> 24:49.705
-Can you feel this?

24:49.836 --> 24:52.316
[flesh squelching]

24:52.447 --> 24:54.188
Answer me, kid,
can you feel that?

24:54.318 --> 24:56.799
[Sully laughs]

24:56.930 --> 25:01.935
[saw buzzing]
[flesh squelching]

25:03.632 --> 25:05.504
It's almost there.

25:05.634 --> 25:06.983
[Sully gasps]

25:07.114 --> 25:08.855
[distant gun blasts]

25:08.985 --> 25:10.421
[Sully screams]

25:10.552 --> 25:12.032
[gun blasts]
[pair gasps]

25:12.162 --> 25:15.209
-Fuck, it's okay,
Seven, it's okay.

25:16.689 --> 25:17.428
It's okay.

25:17.559 --> 25:20.257
[Seven gasping]

25:28.875 --> 25:33.923
[water burbling]
[wind hissing]

25:38.493 --> 25:43.542
[water continues burbling]
[wind hissing]

25:48.503 --> 25:53.508
[water continues burbling]
[wind hissing]

25:59.993 --> 26:01.560
What day is this?

26:05.346 --> 26:06.173
Getting light.

26:07.043 --> 26:12.092
[water burbling]
[wind hissing]

26:16.792 --> 26:19.403
Go grab them biscuits
before the carnies find 'em.

26:19.534 --> 26:21.057
And take mine.

26:21.188 --> 26:26.236
[water burbling]
[wind hissing]

26:29.065 --> 26:34.070
[dramatic, ominous music]
[water burbling]

26:38.858 --> 26:43.166
[dramatic, ominous
music continues]

26:47.823 --> 26:52.436
[dramatic, ominous
music continues]

26:52.567 --> 26:55.657
[dramatic, rock music]

27:02.359 --> 27:06.407
[dramatic, rock music continues]

27:12.282 --> 27:16.460
[dramatic, rock music continues]

27:22.292 --> 27:26.470
[dramatic, rock music continues]

27:37.960 --> 27:39.092
Hey Seven,

27:40.441 --> 27:42.922
tell us about one of them
books you're reading.

27:43.052 --> 27:44.619
-You don't wanna
hear about them books.

27:44.750 --> 27:45.576
-I do.

27:48.492 --> 27:51.321
-I'm reading a book
about early Christians.

27:51.452 --> 27:53.672
-I thought you didn't
like Christians.

27:53.802 --> 27:55.021
-I don't.

27:55.151 --> 27:56.979
-Then why are you
reading about 'em?

27:57.110 --> 27:59.286
-Comedy, I guess.

28:02.985 --> 28:06.554
So this early group, they
were called gnostics.

28:07.903 --> 28:10.645
They believed the Devil
was telling the truth

28:12.212 --> 28:13.604
and that God was the liar.

28:14.823 --> 28:16.172
-He is a liar.

28:18.479 --> 28:20.394
-So when the Devil
brought the apple,

28:21.787 --> 28:22.875
to our Eve,

28:27.140 --> 28:28.576
he brought her knowledge,

28:29.882 --> 28:30.926
and light,

28:32.754 --> 28:33.581
and good.

28:36.410 --> 28:38.499
They thought the
world was upside down

28:40.109 --> 28:41.589
and if you stood on your head,

28:42.982 --> 28:44.418
and opened your eyes,

28:45.854 --> 28:47.116
it was right-side up.

28:49.553 --> 28:51.251
-I like those Christians.

28:52.252 --> 28:55.646
[eerie, distorted music]

29:01.043 --> 29:05.308
[eerie, distorted
music continues]

29:05.439 --> 29:07.920
[door rattles]

29:11.662 --> 29:13.534
Are we late for dinner?

29:15.362 --> 29:17.886
[lid clicks]

29:23.936 --> 29:27.287
[record static hissing]

29:29.463 --> 29:33.684
♪ When the boys come home
from the eye of the storm ♪

29:33.815 --> 29:37.906
♪ They hope to
find their loves ♪

29:38.037 --> 29:40.082
♪ Who were left on the
shore in the days of yore ♪

29:40.213 --> 29:41.040
-Honey?

29:42.432 --> 29:43.390
-Dinnertime.

29:44.304 --> 29:47.002
Oh Eve, love the table setting.

29:48.787 --> 29:52.442
♪ With a high ho
and a kiss upon-- ♪

29:52.573 --> 29:55.837
[sighs] Candlelight just
makes everything look so nice,

29:55.968 --> 29:57.491
doesn't it?

29:57.621 --> 30:00.494
Warm and inviting.

30:00.624 --> 30:03.845
Drumstick for you, my love.

30:03.976 --> 30:07.370
They say that ambience
is really important.

30:08.719 --> 30:11.853
Is that how you
say it, ambience?

30:11.984 --> 30:13.028
-Ambiance.

30:13.855 --> 30:14.943
-Ambiance.

30:16.727 --> 30:18.947
Now don't that sound nice?

30:20.470 --> 30:25.084
♪ They can blow with a
Heidi ho and a kiss upon-- ♪

30:25.214 --> 30:28.174
-Honey?
♪ The wind ♪

30:30.480 --> 30:32.961
-Oh she just spilled a
little in the kitchen.

30:33.092 --> 30:35.181
I'll clean it up.

30:35.311 --> 30:39.054
-You're upset about the farm,
but the farm was failing.

30:40.403 --> 30:43.189
-This roast looks tender
as as a baby's bottom.

30:43.319 --> 30:46.018
-[sighs] Debts
were outstanding.

30:49.064 --> 30:51.240
-Well you didn't
just take the farm,

30:51.371 --> 30:53.852
you took a little
piece of all of us,

30:53.982 --> 30:55.941
made the world a
little more empty.

30:56.071 --> 30:58.465
♪ With a Heidi ho,
and a kiss upon-- ♪

30:58.595 --> 31:02.817
-I have very nice
things that you can take.

31:02.948 --> 31:05.298
I mean, that I can give you.

31:06.342 --> 31:09.302
♪ And fair sully in

31:10.433 --> 31:12.305
-Thank you for
having us to dinner.

31:12.435 --> 31:14.698
♪ Sail on the waters, your
sons and you daughters ♪

31:14.829 --> 31:18.050
♪ May sail on them
still someday ♪

31:18.180 --> 31:23.272
[pot clanking]
[cheerful music plays]

31:27.233 --> 31:32.238
[pot continues clanking]
[cheerful music]

31:37.852 --> 31:41.638
♪ And the light
just slips away ♪

31:41.769 --> 31:45.164
[record static hissing]

31:47.166 --> 31:52.171
[utensils clinking]
[record static hissing]

31:54.129 --> 31:57.437
[record static hissing]

32:01.876 --> 32:05.924
[record static
continues hissing]

32:06.620 --> 32:09.318
[clock ticking]

32:11.103 --> 32:16.108
[pages rustles]
[clock ticking]

32:19.589 --> 32:22.984
[dried flowers swishing]

32:29.382 --> 32:33.516
[dried flowers
continue swishing]

32:53.536 --> 32:56.931
[dramatic, jarring music]

32:57.062 --> 33:00.239
[upbeat, rock music]

33:06.680 --> 33:10.379
[upbeat, rock music continues]

33:16.603 --> 33:20.302
[upbeat, rock music continues]

33:22.957 --> 33:25.829
-The head of John the Baptist.

33:25.960 --> 33:29.094
[upbeat, rock music]

33:35.622 --> 33:39.365
[upbeat, rock music continues]

33:45.719 --> 33:49.505
[upbeat, rock music continues]

33:55.729 --> 33:59.472
[upbeat, rock music continues]

34:05.652 --> 34:09.308
[upbeat, rock music continues]

34:14.269 --> 34:18.273
[upbeat, rock music continues]

34:23.583 --> 34:26.281
[fire crackling]

34:28.631 --> 34:32.026
[quiet, ominous music]

34:37.336 --> 34:40.078
[Maggie snoring]

34:45.257 --> 34:48.521
-Maggie.
[Maggie snoring]

34:48.651 --> 34:49.783
Mag.
-What.

34:49.913 --> 34:51.611
-Roll over, you're sawing wood.

34:51.741 --> 34:53.439
-Weren't.
-You were.

34:53.569 --> 34:58.618
-I'm not sawing wood,
Eve's sawing wood.

34:59.619 --> 35:01.099
-I said sawing, not saying.

35:02.012 --> 35:04.624
[Maggie sighs]

35:07.366 --> 35:10.020
[Seven exhales]

35:12.066 --> 35:13.241
Ah, we gotta get moving,

35:13.372 --> 35:16.679
it's light out and
this land's posted.

35:16.810 --> 35:21.597
-[mutters] Seven,
I ain't gettin' up.

35:23.904 --> 35:26.254
-Well, save some
wood for tomorrow.

35:29.431 --> 35:34.436
[water burbling]
[birds squawking]

35:39.311 --> 35:44.272
[water continues burbling]
[birds squawking]

35:49.582 --> 35:53.151
[water continues burbling]

35:58.591 --> 36:01.594
[water continues burbling]

36:01.724 --> 36:04.118
Maggie, we gotta keep moving.

36:05.598 --> 36:06.251
-Okay Seven.

36:07.513 --> 36:08.253
What spooked ya?

36:09.384 --> 36:13.345
[water burbling]
[birds squawking]

36:13.475 --> 36:14.868
It's just a bird.

36:14.998 --> 36:19.699
[water burbling]
[birds squawking]

36:19.829 --> 36:24.660
[Canadian geese squawking]
[water burbling]

36:28.969 --> 36:31.972
[Maggie crunches]

36:32.886 --> 36:35.976
[engine rumbling]

36:42.635 --> 36:46.204
[engine continues rumbling]

36:56.301 --> 37:01.349
[bird cawing]
[engine rumbling]

37:07.181 --> 37:12.230
[bird cawing]
[engine rumbling]

37:13.013 --> 37:15.450
[door creaks]
[clatters]

37:15.581 --> 37:17.017
Hi.

37:17.147 --> 37:19.237
We'll take that room
for the night, please.

37:20.803 --> 37:24.285
[engine rumbling]

37:24.416 --> 37:26.418
-75 cents per person.

37:27.593 --> 37:30.857
-Your sign out front
says 75 cent per night.

37:30.987 --> 37:36.036
-The room is 75 cents
per night, per person.

37:37.124 --> 37:37.907
-That's not what
your sign says.

37:39.431 --> 37:44.305
-Well what I say is, it's 75
cents per night, per person.

37:49.702 --> 37:50.659
-Three 75s.

37:51.791 --> 37:52.574
-Correct.

37:55.795 --> 37:58.014
-I'm not counting
75 three times.

37:59.146 --> 38:00.974
Your sign--
-Do you want the room or not?

38:01.104 --> 38:05.979
-Your sign out front says
room 75 cent per night.

38:07.067 --> 38:11.593
-Cents, 75 cents,

38:11.724 --> 38:15.423
per person, per night, per room.

38:18.948 --> 38:22.082
Two dollars and 25 cents.

38:24.519 --> 38:27.305
[engine rattling]

38:31.787 --> 38:35.313
-Uh oh, a dark cloud
just hit Maggie.

38:35.443 --> 38:38.228
[engine rumbling]

38:45.192 --> 38:48.978
[engine continues rumbling]

38:52.634 --> 38:53.896
-Turn around.

38:54.027 --> 38:56.116
-Maggie.
-Turn around, please?

38:56.246 --> 38:57.683
-Maggie,

38:57.813 --> 38:59.424
how about I make us a nice fire

39:00.990 --> 39:02.470
and you make us
something to eat?

39:04.820 --> 39:06.256
-I got a potato.

39:08.302 --> 39:10.043
I got an onion.

39:10.870 --> 39:12.350
Oh, and I got them apples.

39:13.873 --> 39:15.962
I bet those apples would
be real nice in the soup,

39:16.092 --> 39:17.398
give it a little sweetness?

39:19.095 --> 39:20.619
Can't taste the rot.

39:20.749 --> 39:22.011
That sounds nice.

39:22.925 --> 39:25.972
[engine rumbling]

39:27.016 --> 39:31.586
[out of key strumming]
[fire crackling]

39:38.811 --> 39:40.508
Don't that sound nice?

39:40.639 --> 39:42.728
-[chuckles] Surprisingly.

39:42.858 --> 39:44.904
[fire crackling]
[wind hissing]

39:45.034 --> 39:50.039
[out of key strumming]
[fire crackling]

39:53.042 --> 39:54.479
-You all think we'll
ever get invited

39:54.609 --> 39:56.132
to the Buffalo Horror Show?

39:57.438 --> 39:58.308
-No.

40:00.354 --> 40:01.877
Maggie, we don't do
this 'cause we care,

40:02.008 --> 40:03.401
we do this to travel.

40:05.098 --> 40:07.840
-Well I think Eve got
something really special.

40:07.970 --> 40:09.929
Maybe if you and
me piece together

40:10.059 --> 40:13.062
something nice behind
or something good,

40:13.193 --> 40:16.326
and real and not half
cooked and lazy bones

40:16.457 --> 40:17.806
and good for nothin'
like we have done,

40:17.937 --> 40:19.417
we could do real good by her.

40:21.723 --> 40:23.246
Would you like that?

40:23.377 --> 40:27.120
[wind hissing]
[fire crackling]

40:27.250 --> 40:29.731
-Why do you keep
rubbing your face?

40:29.862 --> 40:31.298
-'Cause I got a toothache.

40:31.429 --> 40:33.256
-You want me to
have a look at it?

40:33.387 --> 40:35.476
-Yes please, Sev, it's
damn near killing me.

40:36.651 --> 40:39.045
[match clicks]
[hisses]

40:39.175 --> 40:40.742
-You got a rogue tooth, Maggie.

40:40.873 --> 40:41.700
-Oh.

40:42.962 --> 40:44.398
Get it out.

40:44.529 --> 40:47.793
-Maggie, I was a country
doctor, not a dentist.

40:47.923 --> 40:50.273
-Get them tools and get it
out, Eve will help you, Seven.

40:50.404 --> 40:53.015
-All I got's the hatchet
and some car tools.

40:53.146 --> 40:56.715
-Get that thing outta my skull.

40:56.845 --> 41:00.545
[distorted, disturbing music]

41:02.111 --> 41:04.810
-Eve, if I knock that
tooth out on the first try,

41:04.940 --> 41:07.377
you fish it out of her mouth
so she doesn't choke on it.

41:07.508 --> 41:11.033
If it's stubborn, set the
screwdriver right back up.

41:11.164 --> 41:12.470
Okay, don't move, Maggie,

41:12.600 --> 41:14.167
I'm gonna count to three
and I'm gonna hit it.

41:14.297 --> 41:16.691
-Eh, don't count to three.

41:16.822 --> 41:18.214
[hammer clanks]
[Maggie yelps]

41:18.345 --> 41:23.045
[Maggie muttering]
[distorted, dramatic music]

41:23.176 --> 41:24.917
Hit it again, Seven.

41:25.047 --> 41:28.921
[distorted, dramatic music]

41:29.051 --> 41:31.619
[moaning] Hit it again.

41:34.448 --> 41:35.797
[hammer clanks]
[Maggie grunts]

41:35.928 --> 41:40.367
[Maggie moans]
[distorted, disturbing music]

41:41.803 --> 41:44.327
Oh, I ain't gonna
miss that devil tooth.

41:44.458 --> 41:46.025
Thank you, Eve,
thank you, Seven.

41:46.155 --> 41:50.116
Now I'm gonna get some
shuteye. [exhales]

41:52.248 --> 41:57.253
[shuffling footsteps]
[wind hissing]

41:57.950 --> 42:00.213
[weapons blasting]

42:05.218 --> 42:08.569
[labored breathing]

42:08.700 --> 42:11.920
[shuffling footsteps]

42:13.226 --> 42:18.231
[weapons blasting]
[humming engines]

42:19.362 --> 42:24.150
[gunfire blasting]
[humming engines]

42:28.284 --> 42:33.333
[engines humming]
[gunfire blasting]

42:40.035 --> 42:42.211
-Don't shoot.

42:42.342 --> 42:47.390
[gun blasts]
[leaves crunching underfoot]

42:48.478 --> 42:52.439
[gunfire blasting]
[shuffling footsteps]

42:54.789 --> 42:57.662
[labored breathing]

43:01.361 --> 43:05.887
[buzzing engines]
[labored breathing]

43:06.018 --> 43:08.760
[crunching leaves]
[buzzing engines]

43:08.890 --> 43:12.111
[pattering footsteps]

43:16.637 --> 43:19.379
[gun blasts]
[Seven gasps]

43:19.509 --> 43:22.164
[water hissing]

43:29.476 --> 43:33.045
[water continues hissing]

43:39.573 --> 43:43.055
[water continues hissing]

43:49.583 --> 43:53.108
[water continues hissing]

43:59.506 --> 44:02.988
[water continues hissing]

44:08.863 --> 44:12.388
[water continues hissing]

44:14.347 --> 44:15.609
-Lost my shoe.

44:15.740 --> 44:17.132
Critter must have took it.

44:17.263 --> 44:19.047
-Maggie, your
shoe's in the tent.

44:20.396 --> 44:23.008
[water hissing]

44:30.668 --> 44:34.193
-Seven, Eve should meet
her sister and her brother.

44:36.238 --> 44:39.198
I got no problem with
your first life, Seven.

44:39.328 --> 44:40.547
It's their curse they left you

44:40.678 --> 44:41.809
after what happened in the war.

44:41.940 --> 44:43.028
It's my blessing.

44:44.072 --> 44:45.639
Who'd a thought a
low girl like me

44:45.770 --> 44:47.119
would get to marry the smartest,

44:47.249 --> 44:49.687
greatest doc ever to
roam the Catskills?

44:52.907 --> 44:54.430
-Maggie, you were
a great nurse.

44:56.258 --> 44:57.564
And you're a better lover.

44:59.131 --> 45:03.048
But you know fuck-well I
was a country-hack doctor,

45:03.178 --> 45:07.356
one step above veterinarian,
mostly a couple steps below.

45:08.923 --> 45:09.663
-Bullshit.

45:09.794 --> 45:11.273
My foot's cold.

45:11.404 --> 45:14.102
[water hissing]

45:18.324 --> 45:20.848
[engine rumbles]

45:20.979 --> 45:24.199
[pattering footsteps]

45:32.817 --> 45:35.558
[engine rumbles]

45:38.474 --> 45:41.564
-Oh ah, you're not
doing that right.

45:43.915 --> 45:46.047
You don't wanna
cut through a bone.

45:46.178 --> 45:48.223
You wanna cut through a joint,

45:48.354 --> 45:50.748
that's where the
ligaments and the tendons

45:50.878 --> 45:52.184
hold the bones together.

45:53.576 --> 45:57.450
If you cut through a bone, you
don't have a healthy stump.

45:57.580 --> 46:00.583
So cut through the elbow.

46:00.714 --> 46:03.021
It's called disambiguation.

46:03.151 --> 46:05.937
And then you can put a
prosthetic arm on it or a hook.

46:07.895 --> 46:10.593
Please, stop cutting
through those bones.

46:14.989 --> 46:18.514
[distorted, eerie music]

46:21.082 --> 46:24.042
[engine rattling]

46:31.701 --> 46:34.530
[engine rumbling]

46:42.060 --> 46:47.108
[quiet, gentle music]
[engine rumbling]

46:50.808 --> 46:53.636
[engine rumbling]

47:00.513 --> 47:03.342
[engine rattling]

47:08.434 --> 47:10.001
-I don't see no lights.

47:10.784 --> 47:12.568
No tracks or automobile.

47:13.961 --> 47:16.007
-It's not a dead farm, Maggie.

47:16.137 --> 47:18.357
-Oh it will be if I get woke.

47:18.487 --> 47:20.446
We are not sleeping
in the snow again.

47:21.795 --> 47:24.319
I'm hitting the
hay in that barn.

47:25.451 --> 47:30.325
[door clatters]
[engine rattling]

47:34.329 --> 47:38.116
[engine continues rattling]

47:41.249 --> 47:44.949
[dramatic, jarring music]

47:51.433 --> 47:52.260
-Hi.

47:54.872 --> 47:56.612
I have a fire inside.

47:57.962 --> 48:00.703
If you'd like to warm
up before you go.

48:02.270 --> 48:03.097
I'm Eric.

48:05.883 --> 48:06.927
Eric Johanssen.

48:07.754 --> 48:08.581
Yeah?

48:11.366 --> 48:14.108
[fire crackling]

48:20.941 --> 48:23.813
It's goat, I raise them.

48:23.944 --> 48:26.512
[chuckles] For milk
and for cheese.

48:28.557 --> 48:29.863
-Thank you.

48:29.994 --> 48:32.257
-As my parents did
and theirs before them.

48:33.475 --> 48:34.520
And Christianson.

48:35.956 --> 48:39.525
My home place, when
the great war came,

48:40.700 --> 48:42.267
terrible, terrible war.

48:44.922 --> 48:48.055
So much blood, so much fear.

48:49.709 --> 48:51.798
[poker clanks]

48:51.929 --> 48:53.060
Were you in the war?

48:55.236 --> 48:56.063
-I was.

48:57.021 --> 48:59.153
-So bad, very very bad.

49:00.763 --> 49:04.332
So much lost, everyone suffered.

49:05.464 --> 49:10.338
We had thousands of
men that died at sea.

49:10.860 --> 49:13.211
[fire crackling]

49:17.998 --> 49:21.306
When I lost my brother,
I felt so alone.

49:21.436 --> 49:26.180
So, I leave my motherland
for big America

49:26.311 --> 49:27.268
to begin again.

49:28.269 --> 49:29.444
But for what?

49:29.575 --> 49:30.924
Here I'm also alone.

49:31.969 --> 49:33.448
But now I have company.

49:34.972 --> 49:38.584
♪ Sanctify the loneliness

49:38.714 --> 49:41.717
♪ It's beautiful and hallow ♪

49:41.848 --> 49:46.984
♪ Swimming in the emptiness
so deep that it's so shallow ♪

49:49.073 --> 49:50.944
♪ Jump from burning bridges--

49:51.075 --> 49:54.165
-Oh, that's such
a lovely melody.

49:54.295 --> 49:58.169
It reminds me of a song my
mother used to sing for me.

49:59.648 --> 50:03.043
[singing foreign lyrics]

50:08.788 --> 50:13.010
[continues singing
foreign lyrics]

50:20.930 --> 50:25.979
[poker rattling]
[singing foreign lyrics]

50:30.505 --> 50:34.988
[continues singing
foreign lyrics]

50:40.515 --> 50:44.998
[continues singing
foreign lyrics]

50:49.350 --> 50:53.572
[continues singing
foreign lyrics]

50:57.489 --> 51:00.622
[flesh squelches]

51:00.753 --> 51:02.929
-Maggie, what did you do?

51:03.060 --> 51:04.061
-Germans.

51:05.845 --> 51:06.976
After what they done to you--

51:07.107 --> 51:10.632
-He was Norwegian.

51:14.158 --> 51:16.986
-Is that a kind of German?

51:19.815 --> 51:20.990
-It's close.

51:22.992 --> 51:24.429
-I ain't ignorant.

51:24.559 --> 51:26.387
-I know Maggie.

51:26.518 --> 51:27.214
You love me.

51:27.345 --> 51:27.997
-I do.

51:28.128 --> 51:29.434
-And I love you.

51:30.652 --> 51:31.566
So much.

51:36.745 --> 51:39.357
[wind hissing]

51:42.055 --> 51:45.580
[dramatic, jarring music]

51:47.887 --> 51:50.672
[engine rumbles]

51:56.896 --> 52:01.640
[engine hissing]
[door clatters]

52:03.207 --> 52:08.125
[hood squeaks]
[engine hissing]

52:10.388 --> 52:11.606
Bum radiator hose.

52:11.737 --> 52:12.868
-It's all right, Seven,

52:12.999 --> 52:14.131
let's just go back
to that nice house

52:14.261 --> 52:15.915
we just passed down the road.

52:17.830 --> 52:21.138
[shuffling footsteps]

52:27.187 --> 52:31.191
[shuffling footsteps continue]

52:34.586 --> 52:35.413
Seven.

52:38.590 --> 52:41.201
We don't gotta be at the
carnival until tomorrow

52:41.332 --> 52:43.160
and we're just a
spit's throw away.

52:45.074 --> 52:46.424
Like a stick of gum.

52:50.602 --> 52:53.213
[Seven knocks]

52:55.824 --> 52:57.217
[door rattles]
[squeaks]

52:57.348 --> 52:58.175
-Hi sir.

52:59.306 --> 53:00.916
We've run into some
automobile trouble,

53:01.047 --> 53:03.180
about a mile up the road.

53:03.310 --> 53:04.398
-Oh, I'm sorry.

53:04.529 --> 53:06.270
-Randy, you're
letting in the cold.

53:06.400 --> 53:08.750
-Um, excuse me, I'm going
to go back to my friends now,

53:08.881 --> 53:10.099
uh--
-Very sorry to bother you,

53:10.230 --> 53:11.971
it's just a radiator
hose, it's--

53:12.101 --> 53:14.234
-Oh well, then that
shouldn't be too hard to fix.

53:14.365 --> 53:16.105
-I see you have
an old garden hose

53:16.236 --> 53:17.672
propped up against
your red barn,

53:17.803 --> 53:19.500
if I could just take
a slice out of it,

53:19.631 --> 53:21.415
I could replace the
radiator hose with that

53:21.546 --> 53:23.156
and it would get me out
of a world of trouble.

53:23.287 --> 53:26.072
-Mm, you know, let me tell ya,

53:26.203 --> 53:28.335
there's a farm, about
five miles down the road,

53:28.466 --> 53:31.164
and a farmer who knows
about such things.

53:31.295 --> 53:33.340
I would suggest
you check with him.

53:34.776 --> 53:37.866
-Five miles up the road
and five miles back to here,

53:37.997 --> 53:40.086
another mile down
to the automobile,

53:40.217 --> 53:44.046
that's gonna put me and my
family into some deep night.

53:44.177 --> 53:47.441
If I could just take a small
slice outta that garden hose,

53:47.572 --> 53:50.792
I'd gladly pay ya
double what it's worth.

53:50.923 --> 53:54.318
-Um, his name is Jackson.

53:54.448 --> 53:57.016
I would check with him,
he's more your man.

53:57.146 --> 54:00.541
I'm sorry, if you'll excuse
me, my wife's out of town.

54:00.672 --> 54:01.934
I'm sure you understand.

54:02.064 --> 54:04.328
I don't get to entertain
as often as I like.

54:05.807 --> 54:06.504
Good day.

54:08.593 --> 54:13.598
♪ When the sun goes
cold, the stars go hot ♪

54:14.860 --> 54:19.908
♪ April flowers begin to rot

54:21.780 --> 54:26.175
♪ Monday's clouds
are Tuesday's rain ♪

54:26.306 --> 54:31.268
♪ Wednesday, Thursday,
Friday the same ♪

54:34.183 --> 54:39.188
♪ Like a moon on a string,
like a silvery knife ♪

54:40.364 --> 54:44.411
♪ I'll feed you in
the cold, dark night ♪

54:47.545 --> 54:51.766
♪ Cold, dark night

54:51.897 --> 54:56.989
♪ Cold, dark night ♪

54:58.120 --> 55:02.995
♪ I'll sing this song
so its ghost lives on ♪

55:03.909 --> 55:07.216
♪ When I'm dead and gone

55:08.348 --> 55:10.132
[camera clicks]
[gentle, eerie music]

55:10.263 --> 55:12.091
-Eve, did you move that ax?

55:16.965 --> 55:20.317
You know Eve, these dead
girls are about your size.

55:20.447 --> 55:22.841
I'm gonna go peek
upstairs in the closets.

55:22.971 --> 55:25.452
Seven, quit looking at
them birds, come on.

55:25.583 --> 55:28.281
[pattering footsteps]

55:28.412 --> 55:31.763
[quiet, eerie music]

55:31.893 --> 55:33.460
How'd the garden hose work out?

55:35.027 --> 55:37.290
-Good, but someone
stole the spare.

55:38.639 --> 55:41.903
-There's a special place
in Hell for thieves,

55:42.034 --> 55:43.078
and I run it.

55:44.123 --> 55:47.561
[quiet, distorted music]

55:53.872 --> 55:54.916
Seven,

55:57.092 --> 55:58.572
try that on for size.

56:00.095 --> 56:02.097
I'm gonna keep snoopin'.

56:02.228 --> 56:05.449
[pattering footsteps]

56:18.679 --> 56:21.334
[door rattles]

56:35.914 --> 56:40.962
[slow, somber, piano music]
[wind hissing]

56:45.314 --> 56:49.406
[somber, piano music continues]

56:56.543 --> 56:59.154
[wind hissing]

57:06.466 --> 57:09.600
[wind continues hissing]

57:13.560 --> 57:16.955
[quiet, distorted music]

57:25.659 --> 57:30.272
[door rattles]
[creaks]

57:30.403 --> 57:33.014
[wind hissing]

57:34.842 --> 57:36.844
[door clatters]

57:36.975 --> 57:40.195
[pattering footsteps]

57:47.464 --> 57:50.641
[quiet, menacing music]

57:56.168 --> 57:59.606
[quiet, menacing
music continues]

57:59.737 --> 58:02.435
[door creaking]

58:27.460 --> 58:28.243
[door clatters]

58:28.374 --> 58:31.333
[quiet, eerie music]

58:33.858 --> 58:34.946
[scissors clank]

58:35.076 --> 58:39.646
[quiet, eerie music]
[wind hissing]

58:44.564 --> 58:48.394
[quiet, eerie music continues]

58:53.660 --> 58:57.446
[quiet, eerie music continues]

59:02.626 --> 59:05.237
[wind hissing]

59:12.418 --> 59:17.466
[gentle, ominous music]
[wind hissing]

59:30.436 --> 59:33.047
[wind hissing]

59:34.658 --> 59:37.356
[scissors snap]

59:37.486 --> 59:40.881
[gentle, menacing music]

59:46.844 --> 59:50.456
[glass crashes]
[dramatic, menacing music]

59:50.587 --> 59:52.589
[door rattles]
[creaks]

59:52.719 --> 59:55.461
[dramatic, eerie music]

59:55.592 --> 59:56.418
Seven!

59:58.029 --> 01:00:01.510
[dramatic, jarring music]

01:00:07.386 --> 01:00:11.651
[dramatic, jarring
music continues]

01:00:17.396 --> 01:00:21.661
[dramatic, jarring
music continues]

01:00:23.924 --> 01:00:27.536
[quiet, menacing music]
[gurgling]

01:00:27.667 --> 01:00:29.321
[body thuds]

01:00:29.451 --> 01:00:32.063
[wind hissing]

01:00:40.767 --> 01:00:44.815
[creepy, dramatic music]

01:00:44.945 --> 01:00:46.730
[Eve gasps]
[jarring music]

01:00:46.860 --> 01:00:48.775
[engine rumbling]

01:00:48.906 --> 01:00:50.124
-Oh Lord,

01:00:50.255 --> 01:00:53.388
what time I cry in
the night before thee.

01:00:53.519 --> 01:00:56.130
For my soul is
sated with troubles

01:00:56.261 --> 01:00:59.525
and my life draws
nigh until the grave.

01:00:59.656 --> 01:01:03.094
[speaking foreign language]

01:01:03.224 --> 01:01:07.054
-I called upon thee,
oh Lord, every day.

01:01:07.185 --> 01:01:11.189
I have spread forth
my hands unto thee.

01:01:11.319 --> 01:01:15.584
Thou has laid me in
the nethermost pit,

01:01:15.715 --> 01:01:19.893
in dark places, in the deeps.

01:01:21.634 --> 01:01:23.505
Set apart among the dead,

01:01:25.986 --> 01:01:28.597
like the slain who
lie in the grave

01:01:29.903 --> 01:01:32.601
who now rememberist no more.

01:01:34.255 --> 01:01:37.694
And they are cut off,
[scissors snap] from thy hand!

01:01:42.611 --> 01:01:47.181
[door rattles]
[creaks]

01:01:57.757 --> 01:02:00.325
[lid squeaks]

01:02:13.773 --> 01:02:16.645
[flesh squelching]

01:02:23.783 --> 01:02:27.439
[flesh continues squelching]

01:02:45.544 --> 01:02:47.720
[rustling]

01:02:52.464 --> 01:02:55.075
[flesh squelching]

01:02:55.206 --> 01:02:58.905
-My mother beat my
baby brother to death

01:02:59.036 --> 01:03:00.646
'cause he lost his shoe.

01:03:03.170 --> 01:03:04.432
But I lost his shoe.

01:03:14.355 --> 01:03:17.271
[flesh squelching]

01:03:18.969 --> 01:03:21.319
I don't know what you
got yourself into, Eve,

01:03:22.755 --> 01:03:24.670
but if it'll save my Seven,

01:03:26.977 --> 01:03:28.152
I'm grateful.

01:03:42.035 --> 01:03:45.125
[people chattering]

01:03:50.739 --> 01:03:54.656
♪ Put your head in the middle

01:03:54.787 --> 01:03:59.313
♪ Put your head in the middle ♪

01:03:59.444 --> 01:04:04.405
♪ Then rearrange it and
disengage it from your head ♪

01:04:15.895 --> 01:04:19.899
♪ Put your chin on the fiddle

01:04:20.030 --> 01:04:24.643
♪ Strike the bow in the middle ♪

01:04:24.773 --> 01:04:26.123
[flesh squelches]
[audience gasps]

01:04:26.340 --> 01:04:31.128
♪ Then you can play it,
anticipate it and you're gone ♪

01:04:35.306 --> 01:04:37.874
[body thuds]
[audience cheers]

01:04:38.004 --> 01:04:39.049
[Seven gasping]

01:04:39.179 --> 01:04:42.400
-Pull off that other hand!

01:04:42.530 --> 01:04:45.446
[flesh squelches]
[audience reacting]

01:04:45.577 --> 01:04:47.057
-Yeah, she broke it!

01:04:47.187 --> 01:04:49.363
[people laugh]
She broke it!

01:04:49.494 --> 01:04:50.930
-Yeah, do it again!

01:04:51.061 --> 01:04:53.672
Woo! [applauding]

01:04:53.802 --> 01:04:58.633
[audience applauds]
[whistling]

01:05:12.865 --> 01:05:14.040
-[Whispering Voice]
How does it feel

01:05:14.171 --> 01:05:17.130
to hold the thread
between Heaven and Hell?

01:05:17.261 --> 01:05:22.309
[eerie, quiet music]
[snoring sleeper]

01:05:24.964 --> 01:05:27.575
[Carnie sighs]

01:05:31.144 --> 01:05:34.321
-Looks like somebody cut
off more than you can sew.

01:05:36.976 --> 01:05:39.152
Hm, nice work.

01:05:40.501 --> 01:05:42.895
But it takes more
than a good stitch

01:05:43.026 --> 01:05:45.071
to keep the light asleep.

01:05:46.507 --> 01:05:48.031
You gotta say the spell.

01:05:50.294 --> 01:05:51.948
What happened, did you forget?

01:05:54.080 --> 01:05:57.431
Oh that's right,
you can't speak.

01:05:59.477 --> 01:06:02.219
[snoring sleeper]

01:06:04.003 --> 01:06:05.135
You're in a fix, kid.

01:06:07.441 --> 01:06:08.442
And I'm in a fix too

01:06:10.183 --> 01:06:13.099
'cause somebody
snatched my pin cushion.

01:06:14.318 --> 01:06:18.844
[eerie, quiet music]
[snoring sleeper]

01:06:18.975 --> 01:06:20.628
Give it back.

01:06:20.759 --> 01:06:25.546
[eerie, quiet music]
[snoring sleeper]

01:06:26.243 --> 01:06:27.026
Give it.

01:06:31.117 --> 01:06:33.424
Looks like the Devil's
got a new dance partner.

01:06:36.688 --> 01:06:38.168
Don't step on his toes.

01:06:39.256 --> 01:06:44.304
[quiet, eerie music]
[snoring sleeper]

01:06:47.177 --> 01:06:50.658
[strange, unseen muttering]
[coin clinking]

01:06:50.789 --> 01:06:52.617
-Seven, is this game all luck

01:06:52.747 --> 01:06:53.835
or is there something we can do

01:06:53.966 --> 01:06:55.315
to make them pennies
fall different?

01:06:55.446 --> 01:06:59.406
[coin clinking]
[strange, unseen muttering]

01:06:59.537 --> 01:07:02.235
Speaking of luck, what do
you think the chances are

01:07:02.366 --> 01:07:05.847
of us finding the thief
that stole our spare tire?

01:07:05.978 --> 01:07:07.588
[coin clinking]
[strange, unseen muttering]

01:07:07.719 --> 01:07:08.502
-Tiny.

01:07:08.633 --> 01:07:10.635
-That's right, tiny.

01:07:10.765 --> 01:07:12.463
[strange, unseen protesting]

01:07:12.593 --> 01:07:17.598
[coin clinking]
[strange, unseen protesting]

01:07:20.688 --> 01:07:22.299
What's it gonna cost her, Seven?

01:07:23.082 --> 01:07:24.083
-An arm and a leg.

01:07:27.130 --> 01:07:31.960
-That's right,
an arm and a leg.

01:07:32.091 --> 01:07:35.094
You see, you stole a
spare tire from us,

01:07:36.443 --> 01:07:38.663
now we're gonna have to
steal some spares from you.

01:07:38.793 --> 01:07:41.927
[muffled protesting]

01:07:47.889 --> 01:07:51.023
[muffled screaming]

01:07:54.679 --> 01:07:57.508
[flesh squelches]

01:08:00.902 --> 01:08:03.601
Eve, is that the smallest
saw you could find?

01:08:05.603 --> 01:08:08.562
Well cut it at the elbow, just
like your father taught you.

01:08:10.912 --> 01:08:14.394
'Cause that arm smells
like rot. [exhales]

01:08:15.439 --> 01:08:18.442
[quiet, eerie music]

01:08:23.577 --> 01:08:28.582
[distorted, jarring music]
[Maggie grunting]

01:08:31.977 --> 01:08:37.025
[saw buzzing]
[distorted, jarring music]

01:08:50.082 --> 01:08:51.953
you got your father's hands,

01:08:52.867 --> 01:08:54.217
a doctor's hands.

01:08:55.174 --> 01:08:57.829
Oh, I loved watching him work.

01:08:57.959 --> 01:09:00.266
He was just Dr. Axon to me then.

01:09:01.659 --> 01:09:05.010
I was just around to tidy up,
scrub up the blood and such.

01:09:05.141 --> 01:09:06.664
Nobody wants to do that job.

01:09:06.794 --> 01:09:07.926
But I liked it.

01:09:11.495 --> 01:09:15.107
Eve, when you stuck
that lady in the head,

01:09:16.326 --> 01:09:18.893
did it feel like you
were on a rollercoaster,

01:09:20.068 --> 01:09:23.898
chugging up and up, and
your heart's thumping,

01:09:24.029 --> 01:09:25.813
and ain't nothing you
can do about it now,

01:09:25.944 --> 01:09:28.120
and then you get to the top

01:09:28.251 --> 01:09:31.428
and everything's clear
and you can see for miles.

01:09:33.038 --> 01:09:35.432
And then it's just a crazy,
wild, wonderful ride down,

01:09:35.562 --> 01:09:36.520
did it feel like that?

01:09:42.395 --> 01:09:45.268
Like you forgot how to breath
and then you remembered,

01:09:45.398 --> 01:09:46.182
like that?

01:09:50.142 --> 01:09:51.404
Well you did real good.

01:09:53.101 --> 01:09:54.538
I'm so proud of you.

01:09:57.367 --> 01:09:59.978
You may got your dad's
hands for sewing,

01:10:00.108 --> 01:10:01.980
but you got mine for stickin'.

01:10:03.938 --> 01:10:06.637
[hammer banging]

01:10:15.907 --> 01:10:17.038
-Hey Seven!

01:10:18.083 --> 01:10:20.433
We're expecting a
big crowd today.

01:10:20.564 --> 01:10:24.220
I heard your show's fantastic,
some kind of new magic.

01:10:24.350 --> 01:10:26.309
I can't wait to see it myself.

01:10:27.571 --> 01:10:29.529
-Seven?

01:10:29.660 --> 01:10:31.357
-We're so glad to have you.

01:10:31.488 --> 01:10:34.665
Thank you for coming here
and doing this for us.

01:10:34.795 --> 01:10:36.319
It means a lot to me.

01:10:36.449 --> 01:10:37.233
-Seven.

01:10:40.932 --> 01:10:44.196
[shuffling footsteps]

01:10:54.206 --> 01:10:56.382
I was worried about you,
Seven, where'd you go?

01:11:02.867 --> 01:11:03.737
-I'm hungry.

01:11:06.000 --> 01:11:07.437
-Eve will make
you some breakfast.

01:11:09.917 --> 01:11:12.964
[hammer banging]

01:11:13.094 --> 01:11:18.056
[eerie, twinkling music]
[distant children playing]

01:11:21.842 --> 01:11:26.673
[baby crying]
[eerie, twinkling music]

01:11:29.023 --> 01:11:31.852
[milk burbles]

01:11:31.983 --> 01:11:36.988
[eerie, twinkling music]
[distant children playing]

01:11:39.425 --> 01:11:41.166
-Three cents

01:11:41.297 --> 01:11:44.822
to see John the
Baptist head inside,

01:11:44.952 --> 01:11:49.522
the Tent of Terrors, the
peculiar, the shocking.

01:11:49.653 --> 01:11:54.701
Miss, miss, no, John
the Baptist head awaits.

01:11:57.400 --> 01:12:00.577
Inside you'll see things
you've never believed,

01:12:00.707 --> 01:12:04.232
things you couldn't imagine.

01:12:04.363 --> 01:12:07.192
The Tent of Terrors, it awaits.

01:12:07.323 --> 01:12:10.935
All that they, miss,
miss, no, miss,

01:12:11.065 --> 01:12:13.067
you'll see things
